c weapon</i> and <i>shield of faith</i>.</p><p><strong>During Combat </strong>On the first round of combat, a cultist casts <i>divine favor</i>. The cultist then engages in melee in the following rounds. He uses healing magic on himself if brought to fewer than 6 hit points, saving <i>hold person</i> and <i>spiritual weapon</i> for use against foes at range.</p><p><strong>Morale </strong>A cultist of Urgathoa fights to the death.</p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>STATISTICS</strong></p></div><hr /><div><p><strong>Str </strong>13, <strong>Dex </strong>10, <strong>Con </strong>15, <strong>Int </strong> 8, <strong>Wis </strong>16, <strong>Cha </strong>12</p><p><strong>Base Atk </strong>+2; <strong>CMB </strong>+3; <strong>CMD </strong>15</p><p><strong>Feats </strong>Combat Casting, Great Fortitude, Weapon Focus (scythe)</p><p><strong>Skills </strong>Heal +8, Knowledge (arcana) +4, Spellcraft +4</p><p><strong>Languages </strong>Common</p><p><strong>Combat Gear </strong><i>potion of <i>cure <i>light</i> wounds</i></i> (4); <strong>Other Gear </strong><i>+1 breastplate</i>, scythe, prison key (unlocks door into and cells within area G6), silver holy symbol of Urgathoa</p></div></section>","img":"modules/statblock-library/assets/Covers/Curse_of_the_Crimson_Throne.jpg","_id":"JoeYemeL5NRAyuIJ"}
